26/09/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu on Thursday (September 25th) approved the nomination of Mariana Campeanu, head of the National Pension and Social Insurance House, as labour minister. She took office Friday. A presidential decree Monday suspended former minister Paul Pacuraru for his alleged involvement in corruption schemes. (Hotnews.ro, Mediafax, Agerpes, Ziare, AFP - 25/09/08)
